{
  "texts": [
    "They also do not always follow directions and instructors should expect that students will have different experiences in interacting with the AI.",
    "If the specific lesson or subject calls for tight scripting (if, for instance, a lesson calls for a specific exchange during a team conversation and that dynamic should surface, every time) then the AI approach may not be right for this specific topic.",
    "Instructors can however experiment with giving the AI specific instructions about role, character, dialogue, challenges, and scenarios.",
    "Our prompts allow the AI to guide the scenario, but it is worth testing to learn how very specific instructions that give the AI less leeway to steer the scenario may work.",
    "The strength of AI in crafting simulations, its dynamic ability to adapt and tailor scenarios to individual students, can also be its weakness."
  ]
}